title: Biennial renewal; failure to renew
context: [ยง448F-9] Biennial renewal; failure to renew. The biennial renewal fee shall be paid to the department of commerce and consumer affairs on or before December 31 of each even-numbered year. Failure, neglect, or refusal of any licensee to pay the biennial renewal fee on or before such date shall constitute a forfeiture of the license. [L 1990, c 285, pt of ยง1]
